hopobject.name: Page
hopobject.body: Have you seen any good films recently? pharmacyit.com.au As Winnie works to free Nelson from Robben Island Prison, she picks up the struggle for a free and equal South Africa, eventually being imprisoned herself for refusing to reveal the inner workings of the anti-apartheid movement. (She recites Shakespeare and talks to roaches to retain her sanity during solitary confinement.) An officious government leader (Elias Koteas) cannot figure out how to break her spirit, so eventually gives up and orders her release.
